  <Name>k__BackingField: Zephaniah
  fancyName: 
  nickname: zep
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Judah\u2019s Impending Judgment"
      title: "Judah\u2019s Impending Judgment"
      number: 1
      content: 'The word of Yahweh that came to Zephaniah the son of Cushi, the son
        of Gedaliah, the son of Amariah, the son of Hezekiah, in the days of Josiah
        son of Amon, king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI will surely destroy everything from the face of the earth\u201D\u2014a
        declaration of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CI will destroy humanity and beast; I will destroy the birds
        of the sky and the fish of the sea, and the stumbling blocks with the wicked.
        And I will cut off humankind from the face of the earth\u201D\u2014a declaration
        of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CAnd I will stretch out my hand against Judah and against all
        the inhabitants of Jerusalem. And I will cut off from this place the remnant
        of Baal, and the name of idolatrous priests with the priests,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and those who bow down on the rooftops to the host of heaven, and
        those who bow down, swearing to Yahweh but also swearing by Milkom,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and those who turned back from following Yahweh, and who did not
        seek Yahweh, and did not inquire of him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Be silent before the Lord Yahweh, for the day of Yahweh draws near,
        for Yahweh has provided a sacrifice and has consecrated his guests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And it shall be that on the day of the sacrifice of Yahweh, I will
        punish the officials and the sons of the king and those who dress in foreign
        clothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And on that day I will punish all who leap over the threshold, who
        fill up the house of their master with violence and deceit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAnd there shall be on that day\u201D\u2014a declaration of
        Yahweh\u2014 \u201Ca loud outcry from the Fish Gate, and a wailing from the
        Second District, and a loud crashing from the hills. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The inhabitants of the Mortar shall wail, for all the traders have
        perished; all who trade with silver have been cut off. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And it shall be that at that time I will search Jerusalem with lamps,
        and I will punish the men whose senses are dulled from drinking,  who say
        in their hearts, \u2018Yahweh will not do good, nor will he do evil.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then their wealth shall be as plunder, and their homes as desolation.
        And they shall build their houses and not inhabit them, and they shall plant
        vineyards and not drink their wine.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The great day of Yahweh draws near; it is near and coming very swiftly.
        The sound of the day of Yahweh is bitterness; there, a warrior cries out! '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'That day will be a day of wrath, a day of trouble and distress, a
        day of disaster and ruination, a day of darkness and deep gloom, a day of
        clouds and thick clouds,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'a day of trumpet and trumpet blast against the fortified cities and
        against the high corner towers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And I will bring distress to all humankind, and they shall walk about
        like the blind, for they sinned against Yahweh; their blood shall be poured
        out like dust and their entrails like dung. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Moreover, their silver and their gold will not be able to save them
        on the day of the wrath of Yahweh. And in the fire of his zeal, the whole
        land shall be consumed, for a terrifying end he shall make for all the inhabitants
        of the land. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Judgment of Judah\u2019s Enemies"
      title: "Judgment of Judah\u2019s Enemies"
      number: 1
      content: 'Gather yourselves together! Now gather together, O nation having
        no shame! '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Before the birth of the decree, the day flies away like chaff; before
        the fierce anger of Yahweh overtakes you; before the day of the anger of
        Yahweh overtakes you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Seek Yahweh, all you afflicted of the land who have fulfilled his
        law; seek righteousness; seek humility. Perhaps you will be concealed on
        the day of the anger of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For Gaza will be abandoned, and Ashkelon as a desolation. As for
        Ashdod, at noon they will drive her away, and Ekron shall be uprooted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Woe to you, inhabitants of the region of the sea, people of the Kerethites!
        The word of Yahweh is against you, O Canaan, land of the Philistines. I will
        destroy you until there is no inhabitant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And you, O region of the sea, shall become pastures and meadows for
        shepherds and sheep pens for the flocks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And it shall become a region for the remnant of the house of Judah;
        upon them they shall graze, and in the houses of Ashkelon they shall lie
        down in the evening. For Yahweh their God shall be mindful of them, and he
        will restore their fortunes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I have heard the reproaches of Moab and the scorning of the Ammonites, 
        with which they have taunted my nation and made boasts against their territory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CTherefore, as I live\u201D\u2014a declaration of Yahweh of
        hosts, the God of Israel\u2014 \u201CMoab shall be as Sodom, and the Ammonites
        like Gomorrah, a place of weeds and salt pits and a desolation forever. The
        remnant of my people shall plunder them, and the remainder of my nation shall
        possess them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'This shall be for them in place of their pride because they mocked
        and boasted against the people of Yahweh of hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Yahweh will be awesome against them, for he will destroy all the
        gods of the earth and all the lands of the nations; each in its place will
        bow down to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'You also, O Cushites, they shall be killed by my sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he will stretch out his hand against the north, and he will destroy
        Assyria and will make Nineveh a desolation, a dry wasteland like the desert. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Herds shall lie down in her midst, every wild animal of a nation;
        even the desert owl and the screech owl shall lodge on her capitals. A voice
        shall hoot in the window; rubble on the threshold; for the cedar is laid
        bare. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "This is the city of rejoicing that lived securely; the one saying
        in her heart, \u201CI am, and there is none besides me.\u201D  How she has
        become a desolation, a lair for wild animals! Everyone who passes by her
        hisses and shakes his fist. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment of Jerusalem and the Nations'
      title: Judgment of Jerusalem and the Nations
      number: 1
      content: 'Woe to you, O rebellious and defiled one! The oppressing city! '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'She listens to no voice; she does not accept correction. In Yahweh
        she does not trust; to her God she does not draw near. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Her officials in her midst are roaring lions; her judges are evening
        wolves; they leave nothing until the morning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Her prophets are arrogant men of treachery; her priests have defiled
        that which is holy; they do violence to the law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Yahweh is righteous in her midst; he does not do wickedness. Morning
        by morning he renders his judgment; at dawn he does not fail, but an evil
        one knows no shame. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CI have cut off nations; their strongholds are deserted. I have
        laid waste their streets, so that none pass through. Their cities have been
        destroyed and are without a man, without an inhabitant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I have said, \u2018Surely she will fear me; she will accept discipline.
        Then her dwelling place will not be cut down, nor all that I have brought
        upon her.\u2019 Surely they rise early; they make all their deeds corrupt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CTherefore, wait for me\u201D\u2014a declaration of Yahweh\u2014
        \u201Cfor the day of my rising as a witness. For my decision is to gather
        nations, to assemble kingdoms, to pour out my wrath upon them, all my burning
        anger. For by the fire of my anger all the land shall be consumed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Because then I will make the speech of the nations pure;  that all
        of them might call on the name of Yahweh, to serve him in unison.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'From beyond the rivers of Cush my worshipers and the daughter of
        my scattered ones shall bring my offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'On that day you shall not be humiliated on account of all your deeds
        by which you have rebelled against me. For then I shall remove from your
        midst those exulting in your pride, and you shall no longer be haughty in
        my holy mountain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I will leave in your midst a people afflicted and poor, and they
        shall take refuge in the name of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The remnant of Israel shall not do wickedness; they shall not speak
        deception, nor shall a deceitful tongue be found in their mouth. For they
        shall graze and lie down, and none shall frighten them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Shout for joy, O daughter of Zion! Cry aloud, O Israel! Rejoice and
        be jubilant with all your heart, O daughter of Jerusalem! '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Yahweh has annulled your judgments; he has turned away your enemies.
        The king of Israel, Yahweh, is in your midst; you shall no longer fear misfortune. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "On that day it shall be said to Jerusalem, \u201CFear not, O Zion;
        your hands shall not hang limp. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Yahweh your God is in your midst; a mighty warrior who saves. He
        shall rejoice over you with joy; he renews you in his love; he will exult
        over you with singing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I will gather those of you grieving on account of the feast; they
        were raising against her a reproach. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Behold, at that time I will deal with all your oppressors; I will
        save the lame and gather the outcast. I will change them from shame to glory
        and renown throughout the whole world. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "At that time I will bring you in; at the time of my gathering you
        together. For I will make you renowned and praised among all the nations
        of the earth when I restore your fortunes before your eyes,\u201D says Yahweh. "
      comments: []
